org.chronos.chronograph.api.builder.query

Interface GraphQueryBaseBuilder<E extends org.apache.tinkerpop.gremlin.structure.Element,SELF extends GraphQueryBaseBuilder<E,?>>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of elements returned by the resulting query.
    SELF - The dynamic type of this to return for method chaining.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    GraphFinalizableQueryBuilder<E>, GraphQueryBuilder<E>

    public interface GraphQueryBaseBuilder<E extends org.apache.tinkerpop.gremlin.structure.Element,SELF extends GraphQueryBaseBuilder<E,?>>
    A base interface for the fluent GraphQueryBuilder API.

    Specifies a couple of methods several builders have in common.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      SELF begin()

    • Method Detail

      • begin

        SELF begin()
        Starts a new "begin-end" pair.

        Begin-end blocks are useful when the standard precedences of "and", "or" and "not" are not desired.

        When calling this method, it is the caller's responsibility to call end() as well. Unbalanced calls of begin() and end() will result in exceptions during query execution.

        Returns:
        The next builder step, for method chaining. Never null.

      • end

        SELF end()
        Closes a "begin-end" pair.

        Begin-end blocks are useful when the standard precedences of "and", "or" and "not" are not desired.

        When calling this method, it is the caller's responsibility to call begin() beforehand. Unbalanced calls of begin() and end() will result in exceptions during query execution.

        Returns:
        The next builder step, for method chaining. Never null.

      • not

        SELF not()
        Negates the condition specified after calling this method.

        Please note that the precedence order is:

        1. not()
        2. and()
        3. or()
        If you require a different ordering, please use begin()-end() braces.
        Returns:
        The next builder step, for method chaining. Never null.
